snippet.title: How to Change Github Repository From Private to Public 2020
snippet.description:

Make sure that you understand that anyone can see your code if you set your repository to public visibility. All the new publishes will be shown as an activity.

It's deep in their bones they‚Äôll run into smoke when the fire is fierce
'Oh pick yourself up, ‚Äòcause

Legends Never Die

'Oh pick yourself up, ‚Äòcause

Legends Never Die when the world is calling you

Legends Never Die they become a part of you

Pick yourself up once more

Yeah, breakfast at Tiffany's and bottles of bubbles
Girls with tattoos who like getting in trouble
Lashes and diamonds, ATM machines
Buy myself all of my favorite things (yeah)

Write my own checks like I write what I sing, yeah (yeah)

Shoot, go from the store to the booth
Make it all back in one loop, give me the loot
Never mind, I got the juice
Nothing but net when we shoot
Look at my neck, look at my jet
Ain't got enough money to pay me respect
Ain't no budget when I'm on the set
If I like it, then that's what I get, yeah
I want it, I got it, I want it, I got it (yeah)

Food is arguably the best thing about being alive. No other bodily pleasure is enjoyed multiple times every day and never gets old. It is an expression of culture, our parents' love and a means of celebration or comfort. That‚Äôs why it hits a special nerve when we are told we should change what and how we eat to fight rapid climate change. One of the most delicious foods, meat, gets the worst press. It doesn‚Äôt help that the topic is really hard to properly research yourself and debates get emotional quickly. But clearly science can give us an answer!

snippet.title: Il √©tait une fois le mus√©e du Louvre | ARTE
snippet.description:

snippet.title: Hypermarch√©s, la chute de l'empire | ARTE
snippet.description:
Disponible jusqu'au 11/04/2022
Menac√©s par les g√©ants du num√©rique et de nouveaux usages, les acteurs historiques de la grande distribution luttent sans merci pour assurer la p√©rennit√© de leur mod√®le. Une enqu√™te fouill√©e, men√©e par le journaliste d'investigation R√©mi Delescluse.

Aujourd'hui pourtant, le pionnier fran√ßais, comme ses concurrents, a un genou √† terre. En cause notamment, la crise du gigantisme, associ√© √† une d√©shumanisation du commerce et √† la surconsommation, point√©e du doigt √† l'heure des grands d√©fis √©cologiques. Selon les experts, la toute-puissance de certains groupes serait menac√©e d'ici dix ans. D√©sormais, tout le secteur cherche √† sauver ce qui peut l'√™tre, quitte √† verser dans des pratiques √† la limite de la l√©galit√©. Pour obtenir des prix toujours plus bas, sans lesquels elles seraient d√©sert√©es, les grandes enseignes mettent les fournisseurs sous pression au cours de ren√©gociations annuelles r√©put√©es difficiles : entretiens dans des box minuscules √† la temp√©rature trafiqu√©e, chaises bancales sabot√©es pour l'inconfort, discriminations sexistes, violence verbale... Comme le formule le directeur d'un grand groupe, dont les propos sont rapport√©s dans le documentaire, "ce qui est important, c'est de briser les jambes des fournisseurs. Une fois au sol, on commence √† n√©gocier". Sans compter les contrats qui gardent captifs les franchis√©s ou les nouvelles alliances europ√©ennes de centrales d'achats, particuli√®rement opaques, qui facturent aux fournisseurs des services qualifi√©s par certains de "fictifs".¬†

La loi du plus fort ¬†
La peur de dispara√Ætre pousse les grandes enseignes √† toujours plus d‚Äôagressivit√©. Dans leur ligne de mire, les plates-formes d'e-commerce, qui pourraient bient√¥t pr√©cipiter leur ruine. Trois ans √† peine apr√®s avoir rachet√© pour 13 milliards de dollars Whole Foods, Amazon a d√©j√† lanc√© sa propre enseigne, Amazon Fresh : des magasins dans lesquels les Caddies connect√©s am√©liorent l'exp√©rience de clients fid√©lis√©s par abonnement et dont les moindres donn√©es sont collect√©es. Plongeant au c≈ìur des sombres pratiques de la grande distribution, le documentaire de R√©mi Delescluse propose un √©tat des lieux mondial du secteur, soumis √† la loi du plus fort, et s‚Äôinterroge sur son futur. Certains pr√©disent la domination prochaine des nouveaux venus, de l‚Äôapprovisionnement √† la distribution, comme c‚Äôest le cas en Chine. snippet.description:
Obtiens ton Coaching gratuit üëâ https://bit.ly/3Cm133o 

Salut √† vous guerriers !
Je suis Myw, main Garen (mais pas que) depuis maintenant pas mal de temps j'esp√®re pouvoir, par le biais de cette cha√Æne, vous faire marrer et vous aider √† monter en elo !

Bronze, argent, or, platine, diamant, ma√Ætre, grand ma√Ætre, challenger, j'ai tout travers√© !
Bon... ok, pas encore le challenger avec Garen mais peut-√™tre cela sera-t-il le cas lorsqu'il se fera √©ventuellement buff plus tard, rappelons que le champion est tr√®s faible √† haut rang malheureusement !

J'ai commenc√© la v√©ritable comp√©tition en tant que toplaner chez Lemondogs en saison 3, seulement les choses se sont mal pass√©es en interne et la team s'est rapidement dissoute, j'ai donc par la suite cr√©√© les FDP (fr√®res du purgatoire) avec mes amis forts au jeu dont Sardoche qui, rappelons-le, est midlaner √† la base mais avait accept√© de jouer support malgr√© tout pour compl√©ter l'√©quipe !

Ne me demandez pas comment j'ai pu avoir l'imagination de trouver un nom d'√©quipe dot√© d'un tel acronyme, je n'en ai moi-m√™me pas la moindre id√©e‚Ä¶
En tout cas, c'est depuis les FDP que j'ai commenc√© √† encha√Æner les comp√©titions et les victoires √©crasantes, nous sacrant mes √©quipiers et moi plusieurs fois champions de France.

Le poste d'ADC et le jeu ayant trop chang√© comp√©titivement, j'ai d√©cid√© de me retirer du circuit professionnel au m√™me moment o√π j'ai commenc√© √† jouer Garen pour me consacrer principalement au streaming.

snippet.title: Get Jinxed (ft. Djerv) | Official Music Video - League of Legends
snippet.description:
Download and Play League of Legends: http://signup.leagueoflegends.com

Jinx's dreams come alive in a hexplosive sequence packed with bombs and bullets and her unique take on fun. Marvel at the mayhem in the Jinx music video.

Vocals by: Agnete Kj√∏lsrud from the band Djerv. 
Soundcloud: https://soundcloud.com/leagueoflegends/get-jinxed

Lyrics:

[Intro]
Blah blah blablah.

[Verse 1]
Wanna join me, come and play.
But I might shoot you, in your face.
Bombs and bullets will, do the trick.
What we need here, is a little bit of panic!

Do you ever wanna catch me?
Right now I'm feeling ignored!
So can you try a little harder?
I'm really getting bored!

[Chorus]
Come on, shoot faster,
Just a little bit of energy!
I wanna try something fun right now,
I guess some people call it anarchy!

Let's blow this city to ashes, 
And see what Pow-Pow thinks.
It's such pathetic neatness,
But not for long 'cause it'll get jinxed!

[Verse 2]
So much better, so much fun.
Let's start from scratch and, blow up the sun!

[Chorus]
Come on, shoot faster,
Just a little bit of energy!
I wanna try something fun right now,
I guess some people call it anarchy!

Let's blow this city to ashes, 
And see what Pow-Pow thinks.
It's such pathetic neatness,
But not for long 'cause it'll get jinxed!

[End]
Come on!
Come on!
And get jinxed!

************************************************

Music of League of Legends Vol. 1

Experience moments woven within the League of Legends universe through soaring scores and victorious anthems. Fifteen new and classic League tracks come together for the first time beyond the game. This is the Music of League.

1. Demacia Rising
2. Tidecaller

4. The Curse Of The Sad Mummy
5. Quinn And Valor
6. Braum
7. Tales Of The Rift

9. Freljord
10. Rise Of The Ascended
11. Daylight's End
12. Challengers
13. Get Jinxed
14. Super Galaxy Rumble
15. Reborn

snippet.title: Feldup ‚Äî A Little Less Cold [OFFICIAL AUDIO]
snippet.description:
Feldup ‚Äî A Little Less Cold [OFFICIAL AUDIO]
From Feldup's album "A Thousand Doors, Just One Key", out June 26 2020 on Talitres 
Available at: 
‚Ä¢ talitres.com : https://bit.ly/feldkey
‚Ä¢ bandcamp : https://bit.ly/feldoorsbc
‚Ä¢ digital : https://bit.ly/feldig
¬© Talitres 2020


LYRICS:
I woke up on my own
As always I'm alone, I failed last night
I don't even want to know
Why I wanted to go, My first and last try
Tried to turn, tried to run
On my way home, chasing a lie

But I'll keep waking up
I don't want to stop
Even though it hurts
We can make this world
A little less cold
A little less cold
A little less cold

I try to dodge the calls
I was banging on the walls, the pain was sly
I can force myself
To be someone else, It's a hard lie
Haven't ever been
Haven't ever been happy at least just once

But I'll keep waking up
I don't want to stop
Even though it hurts
We can make this world
A little less cold
A little less cold
A little less cold

A little less cold
A little less cold

snippet.title: How to Show Positive and Negative Colors in Chart in Tableau
snippet.description:
In this silent video, you'll learn how to show positive and negative colors in a chart in Tableau. 

Read the full article here: Show Positive and Negative Colors in Chart -- http://kb.tableau.com/articles/howto/show-positive-and-negative-colors-in-chart

- - - - - - - - - - - - - -

1. Place the desired measure on the Color shelf.
2. Right-click the caret in the upper right corner of the Color card and select Edit Colors....
3. Check the Stepped Color box and choose 2 steps.
4. Click OK.

- - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Subscribe to the Tableau YouTube channel here: [link: http://www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user=tableausoftware]

Free Trial of Tableau: [link: https://www.tableau.com/products/trial ]

snippet.title: Learn How to Make the Best Homemade Pizza with Gennaro Contaldo | Citalia
snippet.description:
Pizza is arguably Italy's most famous dish and can now be found all over the world. We're most familiar with takeaway and even frozen pizza but once you've made your very own pizza from scratch, there really is no going back.

In this video, Italian chef, Gennaro Contaldo shows you how to make homemade pizza at home - don't worry, you don't need a wood oven to follow this recipe. Here you'll learn how to make, knead and shape the dough before topping with delicious Parma ham and fresh rocket for a simple yet delicious meal!

-------------------------------------------------------------------

Ingredients
(makes 2 x large pizzas) 

For the dough 

500g strong flour 
5g salt 
10g fresh yeast 
325ml lukewarm water 

Topping for Margherita 

150g tinned chopped tomatoes or tomato passata 
Salt & pepper 
1 x tablespoons extra virgin olive oil & extra for drizzling 
1 x tablespoon grated parmesan cheese 
1 x ball mozzarella
A few fresh basil leaves

Topping for Prosciutto & Rocket 

Extra virgin olive oil for drizzling 
1 x ball mozzarella    
1 x tablespoon grated parmesan 
4 x slices of Parma ham 
Handful of rocket 
Juice of ¬Ω lemon 

Method 
First make the dough. Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water. Combine flour and salt in a large bowl. Gradually add the yeast mixture, mixing well until you obtain a dough. Place dough on a lightly floured work surface and knead for about 10 minutes. Cover with a cloth or cling film and leave to rest in a warm place for at least 30 minutes until the dough has doubled in size.  

Preheat the oven to 220 degrees centigrade.  

Take the dough, knock it back, then divide into two pieces, cover each with a cloth and leave to rest in a warm place for a further 30 minutes.  

Meanwhile prepare the toppings.  For the Margherita, place tomatoes or passata in a small bowl, season with salt & pepper and stir in 1 tablespoon of extra virgin olive oil.  Roughly chop the mozzarella.  

Sprinkle some flour onto a clean work surface and with your fingers spread each piece of dough into a roughly round shape with a border, make the dough as thin as you can but be careful not to tear it. Sprinkle some semolina or flour onto 2 large flat baking trays and place the pizza bases on them.  

Drizzle a little extra virgin olive oil over each base. On one, spread the tomato mixture evenly over, sprinkle with parmesan, scatter a few basil leaves over and top with mozzarella. 

On the other base, arrange mozzarella and parmesan all over, top with Parma ham.  

Place both pizzas into the hot oven and bake for 8 ‚Äì 10 minutes.  
In the meantime, toss the rocket in a little extra virgin olive oil and lemon juice.  

Remove the pizzas from the oven, top the Parma ham pizza with rocket and serve immediately.

localized.title: Learn How to Make the Best Homemade Pizza with Gennaro Contaldo | Citalia
localized.description:
Pizza is arguably Italy's most famous dish and can now be found all over the world. We're most familiar with takeaway and even frozen pizza but once you've made your very own pizza from scratch, there really is no going back.

In this video, Italian chef, Gennaro Contaldo shows you how to make homemade pizza at home - don't worry, you don't need a wood oven to follow this recipe. Here you'll learn how to make, knead and shape the dough before topping with delicious Parma ham and fresh rocket for a simple yet delicious meal!

-------------------------------------------------------------------

Ingredients
(makes 2 x large pizzas) 

For the dough 

500g strong flour 
5g salt 
10g fresh yeast 
325ml lukewarm water 

Topping for Margherita 

150g tinned chopped tomatoes or tomato passata 
Salt & pepper 
1 x tablespoons extra virgin olive oil & extra for drizzling 
1 x tablespoon grated parmesan cheese 
1 x ball mozzarella
A few fresh basil leaves

Topping for Prosciutto & Rocket 

Extra virgin olive oil for drizzling 
1 x ball mozzarella    
1 x tablespoon grated parmesan 
4 x slices of Parma ham 
Handful of rocket 
Juice of ¬Ω lemon 

Method 
First make the dough. Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water. Combine flour and salt in a large bowl. Gradually add the yeast mixture, mixing well until you obtain a dough. Place dough on a lightly floured work surface and knead for about 10 minutes. Cover with a cloth or cling film and leave to rest in a warm place for at least 30 minutes until the dough has doubled in size.  

Preheat the oven to 220 degrees centigrade.  

Take the dough, knock it back, then divide into two pieces, cover each with a cloth and leave to rest in a warm place for a further 30 minutes.  

Meanwhile prepare the toppings.  For the Margherita, place tomatoes or passata in a small bowl, season with salt & pepper and stir in 1 tablespoon of extra virgin olive oil.  Roughly chop the mozzarella.  

Sprinkle some flour onto a clean work surface and with your fingers spread each piece of dough into a roughly round shape with a border, make the dough as thin as you can but be careful not to tear it. Sprinkle some semolina or flour onto 2 large flat baking trays and place the pizza bases on them.  

Drizzle a little extra virgin olive oil over each base. On one, spread the tomato mixture evenly over, sprinkle with parmesan, scatter a few basil leaves over and top with mozzarella. 

On the other base, arrange mozzarella and parmesan all over, top with Parma ham.  

Place both pizzas into the hot oven and bake for 8 ‚Äì 10 minutes.  
In the meantime, toss the rocket in a little extra virgin olive oil and lemon juice.  

Remove the pizzas from the oven, top the Parma ham pizza with rocket and serve immediately.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
